Heat the oil in a frying pan. Cook the onion for 5 minutes, stirring frequently, until translucent. Increase the heat. Add the ham and cook for about 3 minutes until it begins to brown. Stir in the tomatoes and paprika. Bring to a boil, then simmer for 3 minutes, stirring frequently. Mix in the peas. Mash the garlic, parsley, and Â½ tsp salt together, then stir in the wine. Add to the pan, and season with pepper. Simmer for 5 minutes more, and serve hot.